<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600 Models
        Built Before 05/20/2003 - ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER AND AUXILIARY GAUGE SWITCH PACK - DESCRIPTION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0825401">Electronic Gauge Cluster</hotlnk>
                (EGC) components include gauges, warning lamps, an alarm, a digital display, a display set/reset button,
                and a switch pack containing up to three switches.
            </para>
            <para>The EGC communicates with the electrical system controller (ESC) and other controllers connected to
                the Drivetrain 1939 data link.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0825401" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0825401.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="532px"/>
                <caption>Electronic Gauge Cluster</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The AGSP has locations for three gauges and also contains locations for 6 programmable switches.
            </para>
            <para>The AGSP gauges and switches communicate with the electrical system controller (ESC) and other
                controllers on the Drivetrain 1939 Data Link.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0825402" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g082542a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"
                         scalefitheight="532px"/>
                <caption>Auxiliary Gauge Switch Pack (AGSP)</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
